  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "16c8bb9e79ac8bca9256d36640182bf9ee733db6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-08-22 04:36:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (7 inline comments)\n\nI didn't look at the whole patch because I think the stuff in llog API needs fixing. Please let me know if I missed something. Thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a049dba8afe80ddb2bbdbc755e2f36628a552da6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-22 05:46:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (5 inline comments)\n\nI am not sure what exactly needs fixing in API? Nevertheless, note, this is port from orion to master, so it is working over OSD already and some not-critical things maybe postponed to later discussion and improvements in master itself.\n\nAbout API semantic - llog_open and llog_close is like file handle or lu_object semantic. Open just create new handler and associate it with existent llog. Close destroys handle. Maybe that could be llog_handle_get/put but I am not sure that is more clear.\n\nCreate becomes very simple and generic - it just does pure create and allowed over OSD only. That is why having thandle is fine here, like that is fine with dt_create in OSD.\n\nLlog library is just extension over dt_object API, all high-level users can use helpers like llog_open_create(), llog_write(), llog_erase() which hides transaction handling.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3de783c9634c89e7607489f18e7be5ff5bd68cdd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-22 20:39:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(27 inline comments)\n\nMostly style issues, since I've gone through this code once already when it was being landed on orion.  I guess you don't have the .git/hooks/{prepare-}commit-msg scripts installed, or are ignoring the output, since there are numerous style issues in these patches.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
