          "tz": 240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
          "email": "tappro@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-09-05 10:12:16.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-1302 llog: introduce llog_open",
        "message": "LU-1302 llog: introduce llog_open\n\n- llog_open is pair to llog_close. Llog handle is allocated inside\n  llog_open while llog_free_handle is part of llog_close. Each llog\n  even non-existent should be opened and closed.\n- llog_exist() is added to API to check if llog file exists\n- llog_cat_put is renamed to llog_cat_close with cleaning up empty\n  llogs like llog_obd_origin_cleanup did.\n\nSigned-off-by: Mikhail Pershin <tappro@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I6360b4c089ec1dde50289563447eefd3dfa4365a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
